## Description

Write function RemoveExclamationMarks which removes all exclamation marks from a given string.

### My solution (without using for as challenge)

// Write resulting string into buffer pointed by `str_out`
// It has enough room for `strlen(str_in) + 1` bytes
void remove_exclamation_marks(const char *str_in, char *str_out) {
  int i = 0;
  int j = 0;
  while(str_in[i] != '\0') {
    if(str_in[i] != '!'){
      str_out[j] = str_in[i];
      j++;
    } 
    i++;
  }
   str_out[j] = '\0';
}


###  Better solution :

void remove_exclamation_marks(const char *str_in, char *str_out)
{
  do
  {
    if (*str_in != '!') *str_out++ = *str_in;
  }
  while (*str_in++);
};
